"title": "5839: dissatisfaction",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5839",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The human feeling of emptiness and unfulfilment, at either a physical or spiritual level.</p>\n<h2>Hunger and thirst are never permanently satisfied</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:7\">ECC 6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:15\">PSA 59:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:2\">ISA 55:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:13-John4:14\">JHN 4:13–4:14</a></p>\n<h2>Dissatisfaction as a result of divine judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:26\">LEV 26:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:19-Isa9:21\">ISA 9:19–9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:19\">EZK 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:14\">MIC 6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Death is never satisfied</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:20\">PRO 27:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:15-Prov30:16\">PRO 30:15–30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:5\">HAB 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>Dissatisfaction is characteristic of the unrighteous</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:4\">PRO 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:9-Esth5:13\">EST 5:9–5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:10\">ECC 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:28-Ezek16:29\">EZK 16:28–16:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:9-3John1:10\">3JN 1:9–1:10</a></p>",
